The following query uses the [$searchMeta](pipe.$searchMeta) stage to return
unique values of movies that contain the term `Gravity` in the
`title` field of the `movies` collection. The index definition of
this query limits the results returned from a
[token](bson-data-types-token) index, where both the
[autocomplete](autocomplete-ref) and [token](bson-data-types-token) types are on the `title` field.

```csharp
using MongoDB.Bson;
using MongoDB.Bson.Serialization.Attributes;
using MongoDB.Bson.Serialization.Conventions;
using MongoDB.Driver;
using MongoDB.Driver.Search;

public class AutocompleteFacetExample
{
    private const string MongoConnectionString = "<connection-string>";

    public static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        // allow automapping of the camelCase database fields to our MovieDocument
        var camelCaseConvention = new ConventionPack { new CamelCaseElementNameConvention() };
        ConventionRegistry.Register("CamelCase", camelCaseConvention, type => true);

        // connect to your Atlas cluster
        var mongoClient = new MongoClient(MongoConnectionString);
        var mflixDatabase = mongoClient.GetDatabase("sample_mflix");
        var moviesCollection = mflixDatabase.GetCollection<MovieDocument>("movies");

        // define and run pipeline
        var results = moviesCollection.Aggregate()
            .SearchMeta(Builders<MovieDocument>.Search.Facet(
                Builders<MovieDocument>.Search.Autocomplete(movie => movie.Title, "Gravity"),
                Builders<MovieDocument>.SearchFacet.String("titleFacet", movie => movie.Title, 100)))
            .Single();

        // print results
        Console.WriteLine(results.ToJson());
    }
}

[BsonIgnoreExtraElements]
public class MovieDocument
{
    [BsonIgnoreIfDefault]
    public ObjectId Id { get; set; }
    public string Title { get; set; }
}

```

```json
{
  "count" : {
    "lowerBound" : NumberLong(5),
    "total" : null
  },
  "facet" : {
    "titleFacet" : {
      "buckets" : [
        {
          "_id" : "Gravity",
          "count" : NumberLong(3)
        },
        {
          "_id" : "Defying Gravity",
          "count" : NumberLong(1)
        },
        {
          "_id" : "Laws of Gravity",
          "count" : NumberLong(1)
        }]
    }
  }
}
```

MongoDB Search returns documents that contain the term `Gravity` in the
`title` field. The `count` field in the results indicate the number
of documents in the collection with the same title. In the results,
MongoDB Search found three documents in the collection with `Gravity` as its
title, but MongoDB Search omitted the duplicate titles and returned only one
matching document.

If you want to see the duplicate titles as shown in the results below,
run the preceding [autocomplete](autocomplete-ref) operator query
without [faceted navigation](fts-facet-ref) and use
the [$search](pipe.$search) stage instead. You must also use the
[$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to exclude all fields except `title`.

```javascript
{ "title" : "Gravity" }
{ "title" : "Gravity" }
{ "title" : "Gravity" }
{ "title" : "Defying Gravity" }
{ "title" : "Laws of Gravity" }
```

